findings.recommendation:
Broaden the catch in observePerModelSettings to include CorruptionException (and IOException as a common supertype of neither — they are disjoint). For save/reset, wrap updateData in a catch that handles both IOException and CorruptionException:

```kotlin
.catch { cause ->
    if (cause is IOException || cause is CorruptionException) {
        errorLog.e(ERROR_COMPONENT, "observe failed for modelId=$modelId", cause)
        emit(AppSettings.getDefaultInstance())
    } else {
        throw cause
    }
}
```
For save/reset add: `catch (e: CorruptionException) { errorLog.e(...) }` alongside the IOException handler. Document in a code comment that silent save-loss is a deliberate tradeoff per R13.

Add a lightweight precondition in DefaultAppSettingsRepository before calling dataStore.updateData:

```kotlin
private fun requireValidModelId(modelId: String) {
    require(modelId.isNotBlank() && modelId.length <= 512) {
        "modelId must be non-blank and <= 512 chars, got ${modelId.length}"
    }
}
```
Call requireValidModelId(modelId) at the top of savePerModelSettings, resetPerModelSettings, and observePerModelSettings. The observePerModelSettings variant should throw IllegalArgumentException synchronously (before the Flow is created). This is a defence-in-depth measure for future callers; existing code is safe.
